#. type: Title ###
#: docs/8.x/fortify.md:112
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Disabling Views"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/8.x/fortify.md:115
#, markdown-text
msgid ""
"By default, Fortify defines routes that are intended to return views, such "
"as a login screen or registration screen. However, if you are building a "
"JavaScript driven single-page application, you may not need these "
"routes. For that reason, you may disable these routes entirely by setting "
"the `views` configuration value within your application's "
"`config/fortify.php` configuration file to `false`:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (php)
#: docs/8.x/fortify.md:116
#, no-wrap
msgid "'views' => false,\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/8.x/fortify.md:121
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
